{"word":"ὑπωπιάζω","slug":"ὑπωπιάζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑπωπιάζω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>άσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to strike</i> one <i>under the eye</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to have a black eye</i>, <el>ὑπωπιασμένος</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to bruise, mortify</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>: also, <i>to annoy greatly, wear out</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ὑπώπιον'><el>ὑπώπιον</el></a>\n"}]}